<span id="freeTextContainer1805719739565146372">Like Rachel Carson&apos;s &quot;Silent Spring,&quot; J.D. Masterson&apos;s first novel is a call to action!<br/><br/><br/>The Scorpion’s Sting is a brilliant tour de force, a must read! <br/><br/>This stunning page-turner engaged and spoke to so many parts of me I am amazed, and blown away. It’s a suspense-filled mystery that took me on a roller coaster ride, challenging to the core my beliefs, thoughts, perspectives and admittedly calls into question my rather sheepish laxity and propensity to leave the tough battles for someone else to f</span>
  <span id="freeText1805719739565146372" style="display:none">Like Rachel Carson's "Silent Spring," J.D. Masterson's first novel is a call to action!<br /><br /><br />The Scorpion’s Sting is a brilliant tour de force, a must read! <br /><br />This stunning page-turner engaged and spoke to so many parts of me I am amazed, and blown away. It’s a suspense-filled mystery that took me on a roller coaster ride, challenging to the core my beliefs, thoughts, perspectives and admittedly calls into question my rather sheepish laxity and propensity to leave the tough battles for someone else to fight.<br /><br />I appreciate Mags—the outspoken heroine—who questions everything and thinks for herself. She carefully follows every clue, leaving no stone unturned, courageously takes the road less traveled, and musters the inner strength to confront difficult and dangerous situations in her quest for the truth, ultimately to save lives!<br /><br />Like Rachel Carson’s “Silent Spring,” J.D. Masterson’s powerful first novel is a call to action! It is a cry from the deepest depths of an awakened human, whose eyes and heart are wide open, urging us to wake up, pay attention, heed the warning signs, listen to and validate our feelings, paying close attention to learning to read and interpret the signs and messages within our bodies, in nature, and in the world around us. And especially calls us to heed the cries of others in pain and suffering.<br /><br />I am inspired by Mags to courageously and consciously take my life to the next level, to step up to the plate and help get the word out about HPV (human papilloma virus) and the HPV vaccine, instead of waiting around for someone else to do this—I Say YES, Mags, the Time IS Now and I sign on to help! <br /><br />Will you join me before there is a need for another Requiem Mass to honor the dead that we could not save because we got stuck in denial and fear?<br /><br />Let’s build a coalition of hearts and hands today!<br /><br />To join the forces of love and light to help save lives, <br />please go to <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.jdmasterson.com">www.jdmasterson.com</a> and click on the Contact Us link, fill in the form and refer to the campaign “I Agree—No Vaccine for HPV.” All follow-up will come from TakeAction@bridgetwolf.com so please add this email address to your address book to keep it from being marked as spam. <br /><br />Bright blessings,<br />Bridget Wolf<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1805719739565146372" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
